{{refimprove|date=June 2018}} {{Notability|date=June 2018}} '''Carlos Abumohor Touma''' (1921 - 2010) was a successful [[Chile]]an of Palestinian descent, businessman and [[investor]] who was involved in a number of [[financial]] activities in the development of the Chilean [[banking]], [[Mass media|media]] and [[real estate]] sectors.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.estrategia.cl/detalle_noticia.php?cod=33294|title=Falleció Carlos Abumohor, Un Incansable Emprendedor|date=September 22, 2010|work=Estrategia Online|accessdate=July 12, 2013}}</ref>
Abumohor owned a controlling interest in Chile's second largest media [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]], [[Consorcio Periodístico de Chile S.A.]] ([[Copesa]]). He had been the [[chairman]] of the [[board of directors]] for one of Chile's largest private banking institutions, [[Corpbanca]] [[S.A. (corporation)|S.A.]], since June 18, 1996. He was chairman for Banco Osorno as well as several other major Chilean companies.<ref>2005 Corpbanca Annual Report</ref>
